org.coniks.coniks_test_client

Class ConsistencyErr

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.coniks.coniks_test_client.ConsistencyErr

  • public final class ConsistencyErr
extends java.lang.Object
    Defines constants representing the types of errors that can occur during CONIKS consistency checks done by a client.

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      static int BAD_BINDING_ERR
      Indicates that the binding sent by the server is inconsistent with the root hash.
      static int BAD_SERVER_SIG_ERR
      Indicates that the server's signature is invalid.
      static int BAD_STR_ERR
      Indicates that the STR is inconsistent with the Merkle tree root to which it is being compared.
      static int INTERNAL_ERR
      Indicates that an error internal to the client occurred during the consistency check.
      static int MSG_ERR
      Indicates that the protobuf message was somehow malformed or of the incorrect type.
      static int NO_ERR
      Indicates that no error occurred during the consistency check.
